Please reach out if you have any questions.

post_text:
Middle School Fall Sports Information:

- Cross Country practice will start Monday, August 24th after school until 5:00 pm. The coach will hand out covid suggestions, schedule, etc during that time. They can follow @ctfpanthers on twitter for updates or email her at her school email address.

- 7th & 8th grade football practice starts the Monday, August 24th. They will get equipment that day after school. They will be done about 5:00 pm that day. They will need physical, concussion, and release forms. Please turn those into the Middle School Office.

- 7th & 8th Grade Volleyball practice will start Wednesday, August 26th after school. There will be a volleyball meeting on Tuesday, August 25th at 3:30 pm in the commons and should go till about 4:00 pm.

Dear Panther Partners:

I hope this finds you well and staying healthy as we all adjust to a new way of living. As the district slowly wraps up this school year, we are also planning for the start of the 2020-2021 school year. We want to be prepared to support all of our students and families to have access to technology and distant learning if necessary. Please complete this three minute survey by Friday, May 8, to help guide our decisions and preparation for distant learning.

Nancy Durand Loudon is with Karen Smith Guthrie and 28 others.
April 20 at 8:10 AM ·

2020 Graduate Banner Salute! We are all in this together!

In an effort to celebrate our 2020 Creston Seniors, and to inspire hope and unity, I have ordered these 5'x2' banners for all the graduates. My hope is that you will proudly display them on your house, barn, window, fence, etc and take a photo of your Senior by the banner. Then, share the photo on Facebook & send in a message to Creston High School FB page (I think that's how you do it!). Let’s flood social media with positive, optimistic signs to celebrate our Senior’s success! Banners will be located outside the Creston Realty Office at 118 West Union Street in Creston from 9-3, they are all labeled, so grab yours! Those not picked up by Wednesday 4/22 will be delivered! Nancy Durand Loudon is with Karen Smith Guthrie and 28 others.
April 20 at 8:10 AM ·

2020 Graduate Banner Salute! We are all in this together!

In an effort to celebrate our 2020 Creston Seniors, and to inspire hope and unity, I have ordered these 5'x2' banners for all the graduates. My hope is that you will proudly display them on your house, barn, window, fence, etc and take a photo of your Senior by the banner. Then, share the photo on Facebook & send in a message to Creston High School FB page (I think that's how you do it!). Let’s flood social media with positive, optimistic signs to celebrate our Senior’s success! Banners will be located outside the Creston Realty Office at 118 West Union Street in Creston from 9-3, they are all labeled, so grab yours! Those not picked up by Wednesday 4/22 will be delivered! Congratulations Creston Seniors!!

Please share with other graduates and parents!
